Here's my code
```
var options = {
	filename: './test.xlsx',
	useStyles: true,
	useSharedStrings: true
};
var workbook = new Excel.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter(options);
var worksheet = workbook.addWorksheet('test');
worksheet.views = [
	{
		state: 'frozen',
		xSplit: 3,
		ySplit: 4
	}
];
```
It's doesn't work
But if I create worksheet and set options like this
```
var worksheet = workbook.addWorksheet('test', {
	views: [{
		state: 'frozen',
		ySplit: 3
	}]
});
```
It runs
The problem is that these two variables(x&y) are dynamic computing, I can't determine the value at the time of initialization.
Please help me with this problem. Thank you.
